<h1 action="/intro" method="post" >Title: Aadhaar-Based Alcohol Purchase Management System</h1>

The Aadhaar-Based Alcohol Purchase Management System is a web-based application developed to make alcohol sales more secure, transparent, and responsible. In this system, every customer must register and verify their identity using their Aadhaar number before purchasing alcohol. The Aadhaar number acts as a unique identifier, helping prevent duplicate records and maintain an accurate purchase history. <br><br>

The system records each customer's purchase details, including the Aadhaar number, brand name, price, date, and time. It also enforces a rule that each customer can purchase only one bottle of alcohol per week. If a customer has already purchased a bottle during the current week, the system automatically denies any additional purchase until the following week.<br><br>

This project helps promote responsible alcohol distribution, reduces excessive purchases, maintains a reliable purchase history through Aadhaar verification, and provides a secure and efficient digital solution for alcohol sales management. It also enables authorized users to manage customer records and purchase details in an organized manner.<br><br>

Technologies Used:<br>

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript<br>
Backend: Node.js, Express.js<br>
Database: MongoDB<br>
Template Engine: EJS  <br>
 
